# Plant Care agent workflow

## Git: always commit and sync

After completing a meaningful unit of work (feature, fix, or doc update):

1. **Commit** on the active branch with a clear message (why, not just what).
2. **Push** the branch to `origin`.
3. **Sync to `main`**: merge the branch into `main` (or open/merge PR if that is the team norm), push `main`, then return to the feature branch if more work continues.

Do not leave finished changes uncommitted or unpushed unless the user explicitly asks to hold off.

Never force-push `main`/`master`. Do not skip hooks unless the user requests it.

## Dr. Plant (per-plant health chat)

- **Route:** `/garden/plants/:plantId/health#dr-plant`
- **UI:** `DrPlantChat` on the plant profile **Health** tab; garden dashboard has **Ask Dr. Plant** on each plant card; profile header has **Ask Dr. Plant**.
- **API:** `GET/POST /api/v1/plants/:plantId/diagnose/conversations` and `.../messages` (multipart: message + optional image).
- **Requires:** `OPENAI_API_KEY` in API `.env` for live AI replies (503 if missing).
- **Web client:** Do not set `Content-Type` on `FormData` requests — the axios interceptor strips it so the browser adds the multipart boundary. See `apps/web/src/services/api.ts`.

User-facing steps: [docs/tutorials/using-dr-plant-chat.md](../../docs/tutorials/using-dr-plant-chat.md).
